# MapStruct

Version: MapStruct 1.6.x+. Use with Spring Boot via `componentModel = "spring"`.

## Mapper Interface
```java
@Mapper(componentModel = "spring", unmappedTargetPolicy = ReportingPolicy.ERROR)
public interface OrderMapper {

    OrderResponse toResponse(Order entity);

    List<OrderResponse> toResponseList(List<Order> entities);

    @Mapping(target = "id", ignore = true)
    @Mapping(target = "status", constant = "PENDING")
    @Mapping(target = "createdAt", expression = "java(java.time.Instant.now())")
    Order toEntity(CreateOrderRequest request);
}
```

## Key Configuration Options
| Option | Value | Purpose |
|--------|-------|---------|
| `componentModel` | `"spring"` | Generate `@Component`; injectable via DI |
| `unmappedTargetPolicy` | `ReportingPolicy.ERROR` | Fail compilation on unmapped target fields |
| `unmappedSourcePolicy` | `ReportingPolicy.WARN` | Warn on unused source fields |
| `nullValueMappingStrategy` | `NullValueMappingStrategy.RETURN_DEFAULT` | Return empty collections/default objects for null |

## Record Mapping
MapStruct supports records as source and target:
```java
@Mapper(componentModel = "spring")
public interface UserMapper {
    UserResponse toResponse(User entity);
    // Maps entity fields to record constructor parameters by name
}
```

## Nested and Collection Mappings
```java
@Mapper(componentModel = "spring", uses = {AddressMapper.class, OrderItemMapper.class})
public interface OrderMapper {
    @Mapping(source = "shippingAddress", target = "address")
    OrderResponse toResponse(Order entity);
    // AddressMapper and OrderItemMapper are auto-invoked for nested types
}
```

## Custom Mapping Methods
```java
@Mapper(componentModel = "spring")
public interface OrderMapper {

    @Mapping(target = "totalFormatted", source = "total", qualifiedByName = "formatMoney")
    OrderResponse toResponse(Order entity);

    @Named("formatMoney")
    default String formatMoney(BigDecimal amount) {
        return amount != null ? "$" + amount.setScale(2, RoundingMode.HALF_UP) : null;
    }
}
```

## Null Handling
```java
@Mapper(componentModel = "spring",
    nullValuePropertyMappingStrategy = NullValuePropertyMappingStrategy.IGNORE)
public interface OrderUpdateMapper {
    void updateEntity(@MappingTarget Order entity, UpdateOrderRequest request);
    // null fields in request are ignored; non-null fields update the entity
}
```

## Maven Annotation Processor Configuration
Lombok and MapStruct must be configured in the correct order:
```xml
<plugin>
  <groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>
  <artifactId>maven-compiler-plugin</artifactId>
  <configuration>
    <annotationProcessorPaths>
      <path>
        <groupId>org.projectlombok</groupId>
        <artifactId>lombok</artifactId>
        <version>${lombok.version}</version>
      </path>
      <path>
        <groupId>org.projectlombok</groupId>
        <artifactId>lombok-mapstruct-binding</artifactId>
        <version>0.2.0</version>
      </path>
      <path>
        <groupId>org.mapstruct</groupId>
        <artifactId>mapstruct-processor</artifactId>
        <version>${mapstruct.version}</version>
      </path>
    </annotationProcessorPaths>
  </configuration>
</plugin>
```
**Order matters**: Lombok must run before MapStruct so generated getters/setters exist.

## Testing Mappers
```java
@SpringBootTest(classes = {OrderMapperImpl.class})
class OrderMapperTest {
    @Autowired
    private OrderMapper mapper;

    @Test
    void shouldMapEntityToResponse() {
        var order = new Order(1L, "Test", BigDecimal.TEN, OrderStatus.PENDING, Instant.now());
        var response = mapper.toResponse(order);
        assertThat(response.description()).isEqualTo("Test");
        assertThat(response.total()).isEqualByComparingTo(BigDecimal.TEN);
    }
}
```

## Anti-Patterns
- Manual `BeanUtils.copyProperties()` -- use MapStruct for compile-time safety
- Mapping logic in controllers or services -- keep in mapper interfaces
- `unmappedTargetPolicy = IGNORE` globally -- silent mapping bugs
- Overusing `@Mapping(expression = "java(...)")` -- extract to default methods for testability
